Notes:
1) The original encoding showed all ##samaasa##s broken 
into their ##pada##s, separated by hyphens. All hyphens have 
been removed now and the ##samaasa##s joined together. 
2) The original encoding also had all ## sandhi##s separated into 
their components. These have been joined back. 3) Punctuation marks 
such as ? and ! have been replaced by ##daNDa##s. 

The introduction of the original encoding:

The text used for this edition comes from the following : 
(ed.)Ramchandra Jha. Vidyabhavan Sanskrit Granthamala, 17. 
Sixth edition.(Varanasi: Chowkhamba Vidyabhavan, 1991).

